In article <CF5MJp.9yy@corner.com>, tlee@corner.com (Tennyson Lee) writes:
|> 
|> Well, IBM, in the US, owns the patent rights to the DES algorithm since it
|> was derived from their LUCIFER algorithm.  Anyways, I recall that IBM has
|> extended free and royalty free rights to use the DES algorithm with
|> the conditions that it be used INTACT and un-modified.  Thus, I suppose it 
|> would be a violation of IBM's patent on DES if someone were to market or use
|> a modified version of it.  
|> 

According to Meyer & Matyas:

LUCIFER is under U.S. Patent # 3,798,359 ( 19 March 1974 )

The later system which became DES is patented as
# 3,962,539 ( 8 June 1976 ).

So the DES patent just passed the 17 year mark this summer.


